This paper focuses on the energy-saving mechanism in green relay-assisted cellular networks, which involves network optimization, scheduling, and power management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization problems, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of dynamic programming suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves power management and energy efficiency, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
